<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870424-0070 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Friedman Industries Inc.</HL><DD> 04/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FRDTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   FRIEDMAN INDUSTRIES INC. said it adjourned until next Tuesday a special meeting to allow shareholders more time to vote on an acquisition bid by a Venezuelan investor. The Houston-based processor of steel coils and pipes said about 75% of approximately 3.6 million common shares outstanding had approved the offer, but 80% is required for completion of the transaction. As previously reported, Friedman agreed in February to be acquired for $10 a share, or $36 million, by John Castellvi, a Venezuelan investor. </TEXT></DOC>